Paper: hep-th/9201063

Date: 1992-01-28

Title: Are Textures Natural?

Authors: Marc Kamionkowski and John March-Russell

Comments: 9pp

Journal-ref: Phys.Rev.Lett. 69 (1992) 1485-1488

We make the simple observation that, because of global symmetry violatinghigher-dimension operators expected to be induced by Planck-scale physics,textures are generically much too short-lived to be of use for large-scalestructure formation.